We can discuss the essays though. Most of us already have but I’ll throw in mine. Cycling evergreen was low hanging fruit, but I went for it. As long as it’s done lightly, it doesn’t overwhelm new players with decision paralysis.

I feel like evergreen creature keywords should show up on noncreature cards. There isn’t an “enchanted creature has prowess” or “target creature gains prowess until end of turn” because that wouldn’t be as reliable or as useful as a flat +1/+1. If your mechanic is getting shown up by a flat +1/+1, it’s got a problem.
